# Wise Security

[![CI](https://github.com/transferwise/wise-security-py/actions/workflows/checks.yaml/badge.svg?branch=main&event=push)](https://github.com/transferwise/wise-security-py/actions/workflows/checks.yaml)

Python library that aims to cater to all auth related needs across Wise's Python services.

Supported Python versions: [3.9 .. 3.12]

## Documentation

[docs](./docs).


## Install

The library is available as a pip package in the [internal Pypi server](https://arti.tw.ee/artifactory/api/pypi/pypi-internal/simple/).

`pip install -i https://arti.tw.ee/artifactory/api/pypi/pypi-internal/simple wise-security-py==x.y.z`

## Release

To release a new version:

1. Create a PR where you bump the version in [pyproject.toml](https://github.com/transferwise/wise-security-py/blob/1db0283f0232137052b4d1c3e42bc0b3e397ca0b/pyproject.toml#L3) (we use semantic versioning) and update [changelog](./CHANGELOG.md).
2. Once merged, create a GITHUB release.
3. Wait for the new version to be uploaded to [internal Pypi](https://arti.tw.ee/artifactory/api/pypi/pypi-internal/simple/wise-security-py/).

## Contribution

### How to install

1. After cloning the repo, install [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli) if you don't have it.

2. Create a virtual env and install dependencies (including dev ones):

```shell
make venv install_dep_with_dev
```

You're good to go, happy coding!

### How to run tests

Without coverage:
```shell
make test
```

With coverage
```shell
make cov
```

### How run linter and type checker

```shell
make lint
```

```shell
make typing
```

### Misc
* The project uses Google style docstrings.
* Check out [Makefile](./Makefile) for more handy commands.

